<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="77" pageId="11" pageNumber="76" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="76">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="76">Sri Lanka. Peradeniya, on rotten branch, T.Petch (holotype BPI [305211]).</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="77" pageId="11" pageNumber="76">
<bibRefCitation author="Wu, SH" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="20" pageNumber="85" pagination="51 - 66" title="Studies on Schizoporaflavipora s. l., with special emphasis on specimens from Taiwan." volume="76" year="2000">Wu (2000)</bibRefCitation>
re-described and illustrated this poroid species as 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Schizoporaceae" genus="Hyphodontia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hyphodontia nongravis" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="11" pageNumber="76" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="nongravis">Hyphodontia nongravis</taxonomicName>
(Lloyd) S.H. Wu. Our specimens collected in the Russian Far East fit well with his description. One of these collections (Spirin 5763) was sequenced and proved to 
<pageBreakToken pageId="12" pageNumber="77" start="start">be</pageBreakToken>
close to other sequences of 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. nongravis" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" rank="species" species="nongravis">H. nongravis</taxonomicName>
available in GenBank. The species undoubtedly belongs to the core 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Schizoporaceae" genus="Xylodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Xylodon" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Xylodon</taxonomicName>
clade (Figure 1) where it has been combined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen, CC" journalOrPublisher="Mycoscience" pageId="17" pageNumber="82" pagination="343 - 352" title="Xylodonsubflaviporus sp. nov. (Hymenochaetales, Basidiomycota) from East Asia." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.myc.2017.12.004" volume="59" year="2018">Chen et al. (2018)</bibRefCitation>
. However, the type specimen of 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Polyporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Polyporus nongravis" order="Polyporales" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="nongravis">Polyporus nongravis</taxonomicName>
possesses small but clear morphological differences from our collections: in particular, wider pores (2-3 per mm in the type, 3-4 per mm in East Asian specimens) and broader tramal hyphae (4-6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
vs. 3-4.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in diam.), as well as broader, predominantly subglobose basidiospores, 3.9
<normalizedToken originalValue="–4.7×3.6–">-4.7x3.6-</normalizedToken>
4.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(n=30/1), L=4.27, W=3.97, Q=1.08 (vs ovoid-ellipsoid, 4.0
<normalizedToken originalValue="–5.2×3.0–">-5.2x3.0-</normalizedToken>
4.1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(n=60/2), L=4.74, W=3.46, Q=1.38 in East Asian specimens). An epitype for 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. nongravis" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" rank="species" species="nongravis">P. nongravis</taxonomicName>
from the locus classicus is needed to re-introduce this species based on modern methods and to clarify the taxonomic status of 
<taxonomicName genus="X." lsidName="X. nongravis" pageId="12" pageNumber="77" rank="species" species="nongravis">X. nongravis</taxonomicName>
sensu East Asia.
</paragraph>
